race.comment: Former Hong Kong galloper LUCKY ARTIE (4) has been thereabouts in both runs since joining our shores and will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell. Will certainly find this easier than what he faced over there and looks the one they all have to run down. CHAMPAGNE TOWER (9) has hit the top-four in three of her past four outings and maps well for this from gate four. Looms as the main danger. BATE (1) has placed over this track and trip and will strip fitter second-up from the spell. In the mix. ELLTITUDE (10) has just missed the frame in two runs since resuming from a spell, the latest effort a fifth over 1400m at Beaudesert three-and-a-half weeks ago. Fitter and worth consideration.
